# UI components

## Rules

1. **Composition** — compound components (`SelectRoot`, `SelectTrigger`, …); named exports. Simple leaves (Button, Badge, Card) single export is fine
2. **tailwind-merge** — components without variants (override `className`)
3. **tailwind-variants** — only when real variants exist; TV merges `className` (no extra `twMerge` usually)
4. **@base-ui/react** — primitives needing a11y, keyboard, positioning
5. Extend native element props in TypeScript
6. **Named exports** — `export const` / `export type`, no default exports
7. **No arbitrary Tailwind** — tokens in `globals.css` (`@theme`), not `text-[11px]`
8. **Tailwind syntax** — `data-active:` not `data-[active]:`; `origin-(--var)` not `origin-[var(--var)]`
9. **Client callbacks** — props ending with `Action` (e.g. `onValueChangeAction`) in `"use client"` files to avoid RSC warnings

## Tooltip

`TooltipTrigger` defaults to `<button>`. Wrapping a `<Button>`, use `render={<span />}` to avoid nested buttons.

`TooltipProvider` default `delay={200}`. Tooltips: `side: "flip"`, `align: "shift"`, `collisionPadding: 8`.

## Component index

| Part       | Pattern   | Styling        |
| ---------- | --------- | -------------- |
| alert      | single    | tv             |
| button     | single    | tv             |
| badge      | single    | tv             |
| card       | single    | tw-merge       |
| input      | single    | tw-merge       |
| nav-item   | single    | tv             |
| select     | compound  | base-ui + merge |
| tabs       | compound  | base-ui + merge |
| progress-bar | single  | base-ui + merge |
| tooltip    | compound  | base-ui + merge |
| popover    | compound  | base-ui + merge |
| dialog     | compound  | base-ui + merge |

## Popover / Dialog

`PopoverTrigger` / `DialogTrigger`: same `render={<span />}` pattern when wrapping a button.

`PopoverRoot` / `DialogRoot`: `onOpenChangeAction` for controlled mode. Dialog: `border border-accent bg-sidebar`, modal by default.

## Alert

Form usage: first error only — `errors.root?.message ?? field…`. Place `<Alert message={firstError} />` above fields.
